> It depends completely on who rebuilds the engine as to whether you will
get
> better specs from the rebuild as opposed to the south of the boarder new
> spec. I know I would have more faith in my VW engine rebuilder than I
would
> in a new Mex factory engine. He's a second generation VW machinist and
> won't hex you with a junky GEX assembly, but Dad still hangs around the
> shop so you have the knowledge of a Master Mentor in the whole history of
> VW engines for backup and foundation. Instills very high confidence in the
> work. Of the many long blocks from them that I have installed I've had no
> problems at all but very few and minor issues jumped on and resolved
> immediately. Superlative business ethics one on one, on it's own, is worth
> a premium in my mind.
